<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<suppressions xmlns="https://jeremylong.github.io/DependencyCheck/dependency-suppression.1.3.xsd">

  <!--
    CVE-2026-41907 / GHSA-w5hq-g745-h8pq  (uuid < 11.1.1, Moderate)
    "Missing buffer bounds check in v3()/v5()/v6() when an external output
    buffer is provided."

    Status in this repo:
      - All upgradable uuid copies are pinned to 11.1.1 (the patched version)
        via pnpm.overrides ("uuid@8.3.2": "11.1.1", "web3-eth-accounts>uuid").
      - The ONLY residual vulnerable copy is uuid@3.4.0, pulled exclusively by
        deprecated dev/build/test tooling that imports the removed deep subpath
        `require('uuid/v4')` (removed in uuid v7+), so it cannot be upgraded
        without patching abandoned packages:
            swarmgw -> request@2.88.2 -> uuid@3.4.0
            ganache-cli@6.12.2        -> uuid@3.4.0
            npm@6.14.6                -> uuid@3.4.0

    Why this is not exploitable here:
      - The flaw is in v3()/v5()/v6() called with a caller-supplied `buf`.
        These consumers only call v4() (no external buffer), the API that
        already throws RangeError on out-of-bounds. The vulnerable code path
        is never reached.
      - None of these are in the shipped browser bundle (build/test tooling).

    Scope: limited to the npm uuid@3.4.0 PURL and this single advisory.
  -->
  <suppress>
    <notes><![CDATA[
      uuid@3.4.0 retained only by deprecated dev/build tooling (swarmgw->request,
      ganache-cli, npm@6) that uses the removed `uuid/v4` subpath. Consumers call
      only v4(); the vulnerable v3/v5/v6 external-buffer path is never reached.
      All upgradable uuid copies are on 11.1.1.
    ]]></notes>
    <packageUrl regex="true">^pkg:npm/uuid@3\.4\.0$</packageUrl>
    <vulnerabilityName>CVE-2026-41907</vulnerabilityName>
    <vulnerabilityName>GHSA-w5hq-g745-h8pq</vulnerabilityName>
  </suppress>

</suppressions>
